00:12:07,363 --> 00:12:10,465
I assume that means you have
all the support you need.

262
00:12:11,745 --> 00:12:13,445
Except mine.

263
00:12:13,878 --> 00:12:16,005
You may have conned city
council with your riot,

264
00:12:16,016 --> 00:12:18,091
but I know the truth,

265
00:12:18,352 --> 00:12:21,812
and I will fight you, I'll stall you.

266
00:12:21,986 --> 00:12:24,186
I will even use my veto if I have to.

267
00:12:27,946 --> 00:12:29,687
(SIGHING)

268
00:12:29,787 --> 00:12:39,748
♪

269
00:12:43,834 --> 00:12:45,834
It's the Pear of Anguish.

270
00:12:46,281 --> 00:12:49,582
It was used on women who
had relations with the devil.

271
00:12:51,378 --> 00:12:53,612
Well, either that, or it
was used for stretch socks.

272
00:12:53,623 --> 00:12:55,763
In which case I paid too much for it.

273
00:12:56,746 --> 00:12:59,810
I'm not easily threatened.

274
00:12:59,999 --> 00:13:02,459
Well then I guess we have a
case what my divorce lawyer calls

275
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:05,330
"irreconcilable differences."

276
00:13:06,139 --> 00:13:09,831
Drop Bill 121, call off the Sheriff.

277
00:13:11,577 --> 00:13:13,577
Last warning.

278
00:13:15,831 --> 00:13:17,891
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

279
00:13:17,991 --> 00:13:25,132
♪

280
00:13:25,566 --> 00:13:27,306
(PHONE RINGING)

281
00:13:27,776 --> 00:13:29,893
Spencer.

282
00:13:29,993 --> 00:13:34,384
Listen, I need you to make a
point for me on tonight's show.

283
00:13:35,585 --> 00:13:39,583
Um, you're Alan, right?

284
00:13:39,807 --> 00:13:42,207
Would you say you're
being treated well overall?

285
00:13:43,834 --> 00:13:45,974
(SIGHING)

286
00:13:46,074 --> 00:13:48,074
Alan?

287
00:13:50,924 --> 00:13:53,464
Look, if you're going to
give the silent treatment too

288
00:13:53,475 --> 00:13:56,795
just don't say anything
and I'll move on.

289
00:14:01,476 --> 00:14:04,476
We don't know you,
and we don't trust you.

290
00:14:06,042 --> 00:14:08,042
Ain't personal.

291
00:14:09,382 --> 00:14:12,302
How I got this assignment, I guess.

292
00:14:16,663 --> 00:14:20,404
They usually give me the
jobs no one else wants.

293
00:14:20,490 --> 00:14:22,490
Feels personal, sometimes.

294
00:14:25,664 --> 00:14:27,664
Things so bad you're hoarding food?

295
00:14:29,254 --> 00:14:31,754
I'm making sure everybody eats.

296
00:14:31,765 --> 00:14:34,825
Let me guess, a job no one else wanted?

297
00:14:34,879 --> 00:14:36,419
No, I just know what people need.

298
00:14:37,258 --> 00:14:39,660
A people pleaser?

299
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:41,760
Me too.

300
00:14:42,246 --> 00:14:44,566
I'm always putting
everyone else's needs first.

301
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,721
Truth is, they walk all over me.

302
00:14:51,961 --> 00:14:54,281
You're lucky no one
takes you for granted.

303
00:14:56,281 --> 00:15:06,282
♪

304
00:15:07,888 --> 00:15:09,889
(GRUNTING)

305
00:15:14,603 --> 00:15:16,303
You're Michelle, right?

306
00:15:16,403 --> 00:15:18,103
No. No one calls me that.

307
00:15:18,203 --> 00:15:21,464
Oh, I'm sorry. Meechelle...

308
00:15:21,564 --> 00:15:23,504
Much. They call me Much.

309
00:15:24,017 --> 00:15:26,217
Don't suppose you'd
answer some questions?

310
00:15:27,293 --> 00:15:30,181
Let's say I do. You
make your little report.

311
00:15:30,192 --> 00:15:32,443
Say the Sheriff is
breaking the law. Then what?

312
00:15:32,454 --> 00:15:35,794
- The Mayor will put a stop to this...
- When? Tomorrow?

313
00:15:35,805 --> 00:15:38,580
Next week? While we sit
in here losing our minds.

314
00:15:38,717 --> 00:15:40,717
ADHD?

315
00:15:41,412 --> 00:15:42,912
I was diagnosed as a kid.

316
00:15:43,239 --> 00:15:45,379
Just a whirligig up here.

317
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:47,550
But the pills really help.

318
00:15:48,866 --> 00:15:50,766
Have they given you your pills in here?

319
00:15:51,207 --> 00:15:53,845
I don't take pills, I, um... fix things,

320
00:15:53,856 --> 00:15:55,656
make shit for people, calms me down.

321
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:57,667
But not anymore.

322
00:15:59,528 --> 00:16:01,010
I don't know what I'd
do without my pills.

323
00:16:01,021 --> 00:16:02,517
I'd be so useless to everyone.

324
00:16:02,528 --> 00:16:04,364
I am not useless!

325
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:05,955
Of course not.

326
00:16:06,734 --> 00:16:09,402
So, the sooner we do this,
the sooner I write my report.

327
00:16:09,413 --> 00:16:10,953
Yeah, whatever.

328
00:16:12,215 --> 00:16:14,155
You're wasting your time.

329
00:16:14,647 --> 00:16:18,103
You want to help us, get us a phone.

330
00:16:18,114 --> 00:16:20,390
I told you, I could lose my job.

331
00:16:21,037 --> 00:16:23,558
Your job. Seems deeply fulfilling,

332
00:16:23,569 --> 00:16:25,569
you should hold on to that.

333
00:16:28,691 --> 00:16:30,851
You're Tressie Loxley's daughter.

334
00:16:32,137 --> 00:16:34,840
She staged that sit-in at
city hall a few months back,

335
00:16:34,851 --> 00:16:36,391
we all got the day off.

336
00:16:37,826 --> 00:16:39,753
It was very inspiring.

337
00:16:39,971 --> 00:16:43,351
Yet here you are whitewashing the crimes

338
00:16:43,532 --> 00:16:45,210
of those who shot her?

339
00:16:45,372 --> 00:16:49,611
No, I'm impartial.

340
00:16:49,719 --> 00:16:52,219
'Cause this is some
kind of friendly debate?

341
00:16:52,493 --> 00:16:57,033
They come at us in riot gear,
with guns, lock us up in here,

342
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:58,594
and you're on the fence?

343
00:16:59,203 --> 00:17:01,114
You think I like seeing this?

344
00:17:01,214 --> 00:17:03,214
Knowing all I can do is scribble notes?

345
00:17:04,307 --> 00:17:07,727
Look, from where I'm standing,

346
00:17:07,738 --> 00:17:09,479
you're all we've got.

347
00:17:09,661 --> 00:17:12,161
That's not true.

348
00:17:12,281 --> 00:17:14,281
They've got you.

349
00:17:15,175 --> 00:17:17,175
Look around.

350
00:17:17,815 --> 00:17:19,516
It's not a burden you've asked for,

351
00:17:19,616 --> 00:17:21,696
but they need a leader.

352
00:17:23,202 --> 00:17:25,802
You're the closest thing
they have to Tressie.

353
00:17:27,933 --> 00:17:30,317
I just want to get everyone home safe.

354
00:17:30,328 --> 00:17:31,896
That's all I want.

355
00:17:31,907 --> 00:17:33,628
Well, except for The Hood.

356
00:17:34,377 --> 00:17:36,032
I mean, let's face it,

357
00:17:36,043 --> 00:17:39,671
if they just came forward,
we could all go home.

358
00:17:43,764 --> 00:17:45,764
Look, Robyn.

359
00:17:47,277 --> 00:17:51,038
I think we both know who
I'm talking about here.

360
00:17:54,739 --> 00:17:56,239
We do?

361
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:57,292
Yes.

362
00:17:57,571 --> 00:17:59,572
Obviously.

363
00:18:01,126 --> 00:18:03,126
It's Udai.

364
00:18:03,726 --> 00:18:05,626
She's the leader of The Hood.

365
00:18:06,310 --> 00:18:07,860
Udai.

366
00:18:08,427 --> 00:18:09,687
She's close to your mother,

367
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:11,502
the shooting must have driven her to it,

368
00:18:11,513 --> 00:18:13,513
and apparently she has
the voice of an angel.

369
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,360
Udai hates The Hood.

370
00:18:16,907 --> 00:18:18,908
Of course she does.

371
00:18:20,268 --> 00:18:23,208
I just think it's selfish, you know?

372
00:18:23,362 --> 00:18:25,062
She gets you all locked up in here,

373
00:18:25,194 --> 00:18:27,294
then acts all worried
when she could end it

374
00:18:27,305 --> 00:18:29,566
by just turning herself over.

375
00:18:30,581 --> 00:18:32,373
You think the Hood should go to jail?

376
00:18:32,384 --> 00:18:34,244
What? No.

377
00:18:35,022 --> 00:18:37,742
Between you and me, they're heroes.

378
00:18:39,163 --> 00:18:41,863
But heroes need to step up,

379
00:18:41,874 --> 00:18:43,874
even when it costs them.

380
00:18:44,904 --> 00:18:46,164
If you're so sure,

381
00:18:46,264 --> 00:18:48,264
why aren't you telling The Sheriff?

382
00:18:52,384 --> 00:18:55,444
That's not my job.

383
00:18:56,658 --> 00:18:58,658
Your job.

384
00:18:58,765 --> 00:19:00,825
I forgot.

385
00:19:00,836 --> 00:19:02,575
Above your pay grade.

386
00:19:02,586 --> 00:19:12,587
♪

387
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:15,847
Mom.

388
00:19:16,247 --> 00:19:18,188
Yeah, but... Okay, but...

389
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:19,667
Fine.

390
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:21,948
Bye.

391
00:19:23,894 --> 00:19:27,377
So, your mom has
everything under control?

392
00:19:27,576 --> 00:19:30,037
She's at City Hall on a
mission to get everyone home.

393
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:32,881
When she gets like this it's intense.

394
00:19:32,892 --> 00:19:34,892
She'll handle it.

395
00:19:37,035 --> 00:19:38,936
She, uh...

396
00:19:38,947 --> 00:19:40,887
She didn't happen to leave any of those

397
00:19:40,898 --> 00:19:44,958
- caramel oatmeal cookies...
- Wait!

398
00:19:45,469 --> 00:19:47,065
That's not cookies.

399
00:19:47,076 --> 00:19:49,497
My family is so embarrassing.

400
00:19:49,937 --> 00:19:52,237
Everyone thinks that about their family.

401
00:19:52,279 --> 00:19:53,851
Yeah, right.

402
00:19:53,862 --> 00:19:56,162
What do you have to
be embarrassed about?

403
00:19:56,917 --> 00:19:59,878
Every family has secrets.

404
00:20:05,191 --> 00:20:07,812
I'm tired of always
being the responsible one.

405
00:20:13,793 --> 00:20:15,653
You wanna go get matching tattoos?

406
00:20:16,746 --> 00:20:19,106
(BOTH LAUGHING)

407
00:20:20,154 --> 00:20:30,115
♪

408
00:20:31,214 --> 00:20:33,214
(CHUCKLING)

409
00:20:34,355 --> 00:20:40,256
♪

410
00:20:40,356 --> 00:20:44,456
(ANNOYING MUSIC PLAYING
LOUDLY ON SPEAKERS)

411
00:20:44,556 --> 00:20:46,556
Excuse me.

412
00:20:47,316 --> 00:20:52,257
I need to pass these around, please.

413
00:20:52,357 --> 00:20:54,357
Now. If that's okay.

414
00:20:55,197 --> 00:20:57,257
Um...

415
00:20:57,357 --> 00:21:01,338
Feminine hygiene is a woman's right.

416
00:21:01,438 --> 00:21:06,318
(MUSIC PLAYING)

417
00:21:09,042 --> 00:21:10,972
- Tampons?
- Mm-hm.

418
00:21:11,859 --> 00:21:14,287
What do you want us to do,
clog the toilets?

419
00:21:14,298 --> 00:21:18,018
Whatever you do, do it quick.

420
00:21:19,965 --> 00:21:24,185
(SIGHING) Thank you. Thank you so much.

421
00:21:25,556 --> 00:21:27,429
Careful. Sheriff might track it.

422
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:35,741
♪

423
00:21:35,841 --> 00:21:40,802
(PHONE VIBRATING)

424
00:21:44,882 --> 00:21:48,963
(PHONE VIBRATING)

425
00:21:50,208 --> 00:21:53,315
- Hello?
- Don't say anything. Just listen.

426
00:21:53,690 --> 00:21:56,677
We're not at the station.
The Sheriff took us somewhere.

427
00:21:56,688 --> 00:21:59,033
A big warehouse, we're in cages.

428
00:21:59,044 --> 00:22:00,910
- She's hurting people...
- Hey!

429
00:22:00,921 --> 00:22:02,921
They drove over a bridge.

430
00:22:05,115 --> 00:22:06,664
Who gave you that?!

431
00:22:06,853 --> 00:22:08,019
(BUZZING)

432
00:22:08,030 --> 00:22:10,220
Robyn? Robyn!

433
00:22:11,335 --> 00:22:13,335
You gonna tell me who you called?

434
00:22:14,516 --> 00:22:16,417
Your mother? That
little lawyer of yours?

435
00:22:16,428 --> 00:22:18,328
Why don't we have a long talk about it?

436
00:22:18,624 --> 00:22:20,150
Just you and me.

437
00:22:20,161 --> 00:22:22,013
Let everyone else go.

438
00:22:22,024 --> 00:22:23,164
Very selfless.

439
00:22:24,355 --> 00:22:25,638
Alternate pitch.

440
00:22:25,649 --> 00:22:30,385
(MUSIC PLAYING ON SPEAKERS)

441
00:22:31,410 --> 00:22:32,416
- Hey!
- Let me go!

442
00:22:32,427 --> 00:22:33,430
- Let them go!
- Hey!

443
00:22:33,441 --> 00:22:36,141
What happens to them is on you.

444
00:22:36,152 --> 00:22:39,753
But you can stop it if
you give me what I want.

445
00:22:40,772 --> 00:22:42,392
You can't do this to us!

446
00:22:42,786 --> 00:22:44,108
Let go!

447
00:22:49,429 --> 00:22:50,832
This is bad.

448
00:22:50,843 --> 00:22:52,327
This is really bad.

449
00:22:52,338 --> 00:22:54,831
What about the Hood?
They have to wanna help, right?

450
00:22:54,842 --> 00:22:56,817
We just have to find a way contact them,

451
00:22:56,828 --> 00:22:58,008
comment under one of their videos,

452
00:22:58,019 --> 00:23:00,479
or we could send out like a Bat Signal?

453
00:23:00,490 --> 00:23:02,490
They're not gonna help.

454
00:23:03,347 --> 00:23:04,847
They can't.

455
00:23:04,981 --> 00:23:06,982
What do you mean?

456
00:23:11,875 --> 00:23:13,535
(GASPING)

457
00:23:14,042 --> 00:23:15,742
I found these at the rec centre.

458
00:23:16,026 --> 00:23:17,694
We're on our own.

459
00:23:18,094 --> 00:23:20,210
We have to get Robyn out of there.

460
00:23:20,221 --> 00:23:22,221
We have to get everyone out.

461
00:23:24,556 --> 00:23:27,617
Okay, um, did she say where they are?

462
00:23:28,402 --> 00:23:29,575
Something about a warehouse,

463
00:23:29,586 --> 00:23:32,186
but I couldn't hear her
over the stupid song.

464
00:23:33,364 --> 00:23:34,953
What song?

465
00:23:36,918 --> 00:23:38,918
(HUMMING)

466
00:23:40,624 --> 00:23:43,524
(HUMMING)

467
00:23:43,912 --> 00:23:45,912
That's it.

468
00:23:46,099 --> 00:23:48,099
- Wait. How do you...
- Because I've been there.

469
00:23:54,272 --> 00:23:55,846
I...

470
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:59,333
I don't have papers.

471
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,880
My mom and I, we...

472
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:05,460
We're undocumented.

473
00:24:06,093 --> 00:24:07,386
David.

474
00:24:14,101 --> 00:24:16,442
When I was five,

475
00:24:16,596 --> 00:24:18,596
my family came here asking for asylum.

476
00:24:21,755 --> 00:24:23,755
They locked us up.

477
00:24:27,050 --> 00:24:29,050
They deported my dad.

478
00:24:31,910 --> 00:24:33,910
I barely even talk to him.

479
00:24:34,997 --> 00:24:36,998
I'm so sorry.

480
00:24:40,224 --> 00:24:45,244
Your sister is in a very bad place.

481
00:24:45,558 --> 00:24:53,899
♪

482
00:24:53,999 --> 00:24:57,040
(PANTING)

483
00:24:59,779 --> 00:25:02,679
SHERIFF: A military man.

484
00:25:02,690 --> 00:25:04,915
I respect that. You're a protector.

485
00:25:06,907 --> 00:25:08,494
So am I.

486
00:25:08,947 --> 00:25:11,647
If this is your "we're
not so different" speech,

487
00:25:11,921 --> 00:25:13,084
you can save it.

488
00:25:13,095 --> 00:25:15,955
But who are you protecting now?

489
00:25:16,295 --> 00:25:18,635
I've seen the tapes of
Sherwood's little talent show.

490
00:25:18,646 --> 00:25:22,506
I can't imagine you have many
friends left in those cages.

491
00:25:23,465 --> 00:25:25,632
You worked with a murderer

492
00:25:26,095 --> 00:25:28,236
just to catch some kids in masks.

493
00:25:28,483 --> 00:25:31,823
Guy Gisbourne's crimes
were never proven.

494
00:25:31,834 --> 00:25:33,934
No witnesses stepped forward.

495
00:25:34,854 --> 00:25:36,443
Shameful, really.

496
00:25:42,884 --> 00:25:44,884
(GRUNTING)

497
00:25:47,370 --> 00:25:49,370
How about a carrot?

498
00:25:49,951 --> 00:25:52,011
For every name you give me,

499
00:25:52,022 --> 00:25:54,448
I'll let you pick someone to go free.

500
00:25:55,444 --> 00:25:57,947
Maybe it will be enough
for them to forgive you.

501
00:26:04,072 --> 00:26:06,072
Stick it is.

502
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:08,720
(DOOR OPENING)

503
00:26:11,126 --> 00:26:13,626
♪

504
00:26:13,740 --> 00:26:15,400
(BUZZING)

505
00:26:16,034 --> 00:26:17,854
(GRUNTING)

506
00:26:19,226 --> 00:26:21,754
Bro, I can't take this anymore, man!

507
00:26:22,568 --> 00:26:24,692
I wish I could just
trade places with LJ.

508
00:26:24,703 --> 00:26:26,404
No, no. Your meat is far too weak.

509
00:26:26,675 --> 00:26:28,675
Far too weak. Weak, weak, weak, weak.

510
00:26:30,382 --> 00:26:32,322
(GRUNTING)

511
00:26:32,835 --> 00:26:34,364
Why hasn't LJ come back?

512
00:26:34,375 --> 00:26:36,118
WAT: If he couldn't
stick up for Lionheart,

513
00:26:36,129 --> 00:26:38,110
what makes you think he's
not out there throwing us

514
00:26:38,299 --> 00:26:39,759
under the bus right now?

515
00:26:39,972 --> 00:26:43,070
What do you think Little
John should have done?

516
00:26:43,170 --> 00:26:45,599
Hm? Murdered Guy Gisbourne?

517
00:26:45,610 --> 00:26:47,834
Do you even know what
Lionheart was about?

518
00:26:47,845 --> 00:26:49,345
He didn't have to keep it a secret.

519
00:26:49,657 --> 00:26:52,009
Let's all just keep calm, okay?

520
00:26:52,020 --> 00:26:54,669
MUCH: We need to do something.
Bust ourselves out of here.

521
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:56,446
I can't take sitting
around like this anymore.

522
00:26:56,457 --> 00:26:57,809
We need to focus.

523
00:26:57,820 --> 00:27:00,530
You sayin' I can't focus?
Like I'm useless or something?

524
00:27:00,541 --> 00:27:04,041
- You, let's just take a breath...
- You take a breath.

525
00:27:04,052 --> 00:27:05,719
Maybe if you'd stop
mouthing off to the...

526
00:27:05,730 --> 00:27:07,483
- Yo, watch it!
- You watch it!

527
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:09,048
Yo, leave her alone!

528
00:27:09,059 --> 00:27:10,719
MUCH: I can take care of myself, Alan!

529
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:13,115
